===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}} – a tree: branches on top, roots on the bottom (more visible in earlier forms). 

See also {{zh-l|*本}}, {{zh-l|*未}}, and {{zh-l|*末}}.

===Etymology===
No known cognate exists. It can perhaps be compared with {{cog|kar-pro|*məŋᴮ||trunk (of a tree); firewood}} ({{zh-ref|Starostin}}) or {{cog|tbq-lob-pro|*ʔmuk||stump (of a tree)}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

The common Sino-Tibetan root for “tree; wood” is {{m|sit-pro|*siŋ ~ sik}}, represented by {{och-l|薪|firewood}}.

